                <h3>Failing Drain Fields and No Room to Expand</h3>
                <p>Conventional septic drain fields fail when soils saturate, properties are constrained, or setback requirements can't be met. Replacement in kind isn't always possible — and regulators are losing patience with repeated failures.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Sub-surface drip dispersal systems work in challenging soils, tight lots, and setback-constrained sites where conventional drainfields can't be placed.</div>
            </div>
