                <div class="pain-icon">📋</div>
                <h3>Discharge Permits That Are Getting Harder to Keep</h3>
                <p>Surface discharge limits keep tightening. Fines for violations escalate. Municipal facilities and food processors are facing discharge requirements that their current systems can't meet — and the cost of non-compliance is climbing.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Sub-surface drip dispersal eliminates surface discharge entirely — turning a permit compliance problem into a land application solution.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon">💰</div>
                <h3>Rising Hauling and Treatment Costs</h3>
                <p>For remote facilities and rural operations, hauling effluent is expensive, unpredictable, and dependent on trucking availability. When haul costs spike, so does your operating budget — with zero warning.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ On-site drip dispersal eliminates hauling entirely. Once installed, operating costs are minimal and predictable.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon">🌊</div>
                <h3>Runoff and Groundwater Risk</h3>
                <p>Surface-applied or poorly managed effluent creates real liability — contaminated groundwater, surface water violations, and public health concerns. Regulators and communities are watching more closely than ever.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Effluent is dispersed below grade where aerobic soil microbes provide final treatment before any groundwater contact. Zero surface runoff. Zero aerial exposure.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon">🏕️</div>
                <h3>Remote Sites with No Sewer Access</h3>
                <p>Campgrounds, rural commercial properties, food processing facilities, and remote resorts need reliable on-site treatment and dispersal — and conventional systems often aren't sized or designed for the load they're actually managing.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ DripSmart drip dispersal systems scale from 200 to 500,000+ GPD and can be automated to operate fully unattended with remote monitoring.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
