<!-- How It Works -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">How Sub-Surface Drip Dispersal Works</span>
                <h2>The Soil Does the Work. The System Controls When and Where.</h2>
                <p>Treated effluent is pumped through a pressurized network of driplines buried 6–18 inches below grade. Emitters release small, precise doses into the soil — where natural aerobic microbial activity provides the final treatment step before any potential groundwater contact.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;">The system doesn't just dump effluent underground. It manages the application rate, timing, and uniformity so the soil's treatment capacity is never overwhelmed.</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:24px;">
                    <li>Effluent is pre-filtered to prevent emitter clogging</li>
                    <li>Pressure-compensating emitters ensure uniform field application</li>
                    <li>Automated flushing cycles prevent biofilm buildup</li>
                    <li>Anti-siphon valves eliminate back-contamination risk</li>
                    <li>Soil moisture probes verify loading rates are within permit limits</li>
                    <li>DripSphere OS™ provides automated reporting for regulatory compliance</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary mt-lg">Request a Site Evaluation</a>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:20px;">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon">🏠</div>
                    <h3>Onsite Septic Systems</h3>
                    <p>Replace failing drain fields with long-lasting drip dispersal. Works on challenging soils, small lots, and sites where conventional drainfields can't go — and where a failed system isn't an option.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon">🏭</div>
                    <h3>Municipal &amp; Agricultural Reuse</h3>
                    <p>Large-scale sub-surface application of Class A or B reclaimed water on agricultural land, buffer zones, and green space — with nutrient credit tracking and full compliance documentation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon">🏗️</div>
                    <h3>Food Processing &amp; Industrial Facilities</h3>
                    <p>High-strength process wastewater is nutrient-rich. Our systems turn it into a managed soil amendment while keeping you inside permit limits — no hauling, no violations, no surprises.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

